<p style="margin-top: 1cm; font-size: 300%;">Lies</p>
<img src="https://i.imgur.com/up1b2JD.png">
<p style="margin-top: 0.4cm; font-size: 200%;">Translator: <a href=https://theark.wiki/w/Welcome><u>theark.wiki</u></a></p>
<p class="title" style=" font-size: 300%;">Exchange Test</p>
<p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Everything that lives is designed to end.
<br>We are perpetually trapped‚Ä¶‚Ä¶
<br>In a neverending spiral of life and death.
<br>Is this a curse?
<br>Or some kind of punishment?
<br>I often think about the god who blessed us with this cryptic puzzle
<br>And wonder if we‚Äôll ever have the chance to kill him.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Operator 6O to 2B. Can you hear me?</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">I hear you.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Roger that.
<br>Now then, I think I‚Äôd like to initiate the scheduled tactical support unit exchange test.
<br>You normally use Pod model 042, but this time, we‚Äôll be assigning 9S‚Äô 153 to you for a few days.
<br>You were told this the other day, but this tactical support unit exchange is regularly used as a test to get information on the Pod; their usefulness, any problems they might have, that sort of thing.
<br>It‚Äôs called a ‚Äútest,‚Äù but just go about as you normally do.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Understood.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Ah, looks like there‚Äôs a voice message from 9S, who‚Äôs already proceeding with the test. I‚Äôm playing it back for you now.</p><p class="para"><em>(The sound of data being played)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">9S
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Ummm‚Ä¶‚Ä¶hellooo? Can you hear me, ma‚Äôam?
This is 9S. I‚Äôm doing my best on this exchange test with the unsociable Pod 042.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 042
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Negative: Tactical support units do not have emotions.
The expression ‚Äúunsociable‚Äù is inappropriate.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">9S
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶is what I‚Äôm dealing with. Well, I‚Äôll try to enjoy it.
Ah, one more thing, ma‚Äôam. If you get tired of doing the test, please let me know right away.
I‚Äôll do whatever I can to try suspending the te‚Ä¶‚Ä¶</p><p class="para"><em>(The data replay is interrupted by a noise)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Ah‚Ä¶..ahaha‚Ä¶..
Looks like the rest of it got erased by Command‚Äôs censors.
‚Ä¶.W-Well, good luck with the exchange test!</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Operator 6O ends the transmission, inviting silence.
Once the current task is confirmed, a nearby access point is displayed.
It looks like an investigation is necessary for a body transport function error.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Pod 153 to YorHa unit 2B.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">What?</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>‚ÄúNice to meet you!‚Äù</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">......Huh?</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>‚ÄúNice to meet you!‚Äù</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">...What is that...?</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Report: a statement repeated in order to encourage a harmonious relationship between humans.
In accordance with YorHa unit 9S‚Äô specifications, this is to be repeated until a similar response has been received.
‚ÄúNice to meet you!‚Äù</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">N‚Ä¶..Nice to‚Ä¶meet you‚Ä¶.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Understood.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">If the exchange test continues like this, it looks to be the cause of unnecessary stress.
At a loss, I switched focus to the designated access point‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.</p><p class="para"><p class="title" style=" font-size: 300%;">Pascal</p>
<p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">On the way to the target access point, I passed a village of machines. It‚Äôs a village of pacifists led by a machine named ‚ÄúPascal.‚Äù In the distance, the children seem to be having fun, singing songs. It has been confirmed many times that the machines here are strange individuals. There are those who imitate families, those who talk of love, and the children‚Ä¶..
Despite being weapons created by the aliens, they have personalities.
Almost like humanity‚Ä¶..

(Short pause)

‚Ä¶..It is not permitted for YorHa units to have emotions. We are models specialized for combat, after all. It is the most efficient, most correct choice. But, in doing so, I feel that something unseen in the heart is lost. Was our choice truly the correct one? Who would be considered a fitting existence in this world? Listening to the song of the children, I continued to walk the dark path alone‚Ä¶..</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pascal
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Ahh‚Ä¶‚Ä¶and there. I‚Äôll be intruding for a bit‚Ä¶‚Ä¶
Hello. My name is Pascal. I‚Äôm currently the chief of a village in which those who are tired of fighting have been gathered. What about all of you here, on these grounds?

(Pascal speaks as if he‚Äôs talking to everyone at the venue)

Are you not tired of fighting day in and day out? Being given orders by someone, overworking yourselves? ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶If you work too hard, whether you‚Äôre a machine lifeform or a human, you‚Äôll end up broken. Ah, that‚Äôs right. Why don‚Äôt I teach you something nice?
When times are hard, or you feel saddened, sing a song. If you do, you‚Äôll feel better. What kind of song, you wonder? ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶Hmm‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.for example, a song like this.</p><p class="para"><p class="title" style=" font-size: 300%;">Access Point</p>
<p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Arrival at access point marked for investigation.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Check the transmission status and body storage function along with the transport system.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Understood.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">The designated access point was located in the desert‚Äôs open area.
Amidst the sand-laden wind, the Pod‚Äôs transmission light is quietly flickering.
I was unable to see any signs of damage to the outer casing of the access point, so it must be an internal malfunction. If it‚Äôs the Pod, the problem should be resolved shortly.
The sand-laden winds become stronger, obscuring the sun‚Äôs rays.
In order to keep watch over the surrounding area, I climbed a nearby rocky area.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Body storage function and transmission status check complete.
Report: Malfunction in body reconstruction unit detected.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Repair it.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Understood.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">My field of vision worsens as the wind becomes a sandstorm.
I can see the silhouettes of old world remains made of stone here and there.
A strong wind carries the sand.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Repairs on body reconstruction unit. 50% complete.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Squinting my eyes at the occasional strong wind, <em>(light hitting noise)</em>, I felt something touch my feet.
It was a small flower that I recognized.
I remember sending a picture of this flower to Operator 6O before.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">So this is a desert rose, huh? It seems almost‚Ä¶mystical.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">That‚Äôs what she‚Äôd said from the above orbit base, pleased.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">There must just be a bountry of nature down there, huh?</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶Some, yes. I‚Äôve seen lilies, cherry blossoms, daffodils, and even lunar tears.
I‚Äôll try to send more if I can.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Thank you so much!
I‚Äôm going to treasure this picture forever!
Oh, and I‚Äôm going to send you a proper thank-you mail later, so keep an eye out for it. Bye!</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶I didn‚Äôt know until later, but the ‚Äúdesert rose‚Äù is a crystal made of minerals, not a plant.
Still, Operator 6O‚Äôs smiling face on the transmission screen‚Ä¶..I remember it looked really happy.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Report: Repairs to malfunction in body storage unit complete.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">The foundational framework, the resinous material composing the body, even the small systems for weaponry production look to be in working order‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.
I went to do a final check on the access point after receiving the work completion report from Pod.</p><p class="para"><em>(There‚Äôs a nuance of suspicion coloring her final words)</em>
<em>(As if to punctuate 2B‚Äôs words, Pod reports)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Report: Hostile machine lifeform signals detected.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Understood. I‚Äôll eliminate them.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Signal count increasing. 24, 26, 29.....</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶With those numbers, just where have they been this whole time‚Ä¶‚Ä¶!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Signal count once again increasing. 30, 31, 32, 33, 34.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">It wasn‚Äôt that such a large number of machine lifeforms was approaching.
From the start, they‚Äôd hidden in the sand, waiting in a suspended state to ambush us.
That could only mean one thing.

<em>(Pause for a bit)</em>

‚Ä¶..This was an orchestrated trap.</p><p class="para"><p class="title" style=" font-size: 300%;">Betrayal</p>
<p class="para"><em>(2B attacks the last enemy, her breathing ragged)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.(heavy breathing noises)‚Ä¶‚Ä¶</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Destruction of all enemy machine lifeforms confirmed.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">After fighting against 34 medium-sized machine lifeforms, 2B somehow managed to stand up without collapsing despite her lightheadedness.
Having lost two weapons and several of her sensors, she was restricted in how much she could self-repair.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Alert: Combat damage accumulation on YorHa unit 2B.
Proposal: Appropriate, repairs„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄif„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄtreatment,„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄexhaustion„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄquality„ÄÄ„ÄÄ„ÄÄno„ÄÄ„ÄÄexchange......</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Pod 153‚Äôs voice garbles with noise.
In the air, the Pod‚Äôs arms move in a disoriented fashion, like it‚Äôs convulsing.
The blinking of its light shows the irregular state of its internal systems.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">What‚Ä¶..Pod? What‚Äôs wrong?</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Appropriate, re&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; pairs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;REpairs&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; treatment to sy0 m0......h1......</code></p><p class="para"><em>(After 10 seconds of silence, suddenly, the Pod begins to speak at high speed)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Deploying long range weaponry. Activating FFCS.
YorHa unit 2B recognized as enemy android.
Proposal to suspend tactile support mission. Acknowledged.
Begin attack.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Pod!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">A high-speed energy bullet the weapon-deployed Pod fires.
2B just barely avoids the attack.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Pod 153! What are you doing!?</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Unable to confirm destruction of enemy android.
Begin construction of firing correction program. Construction complete.
Request: Application of gravity control sphere. Permission granted.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Without permission from either a YorHa unit or Command, a Pod can‚Äôt use its weaponry.
However, Pod 153 has an internal bypass to its own recognition process applied.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Firing gravity control sphere.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Ghh‚Ä¶‚Ä¶!!!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">2B avoids the Pod‚Äôs released gravity attack.
But her right leg is caught in the radius of the hemisphere.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Long range attack system. High output charge. Preparing concentrated laser attack.</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">The Pod‚Äôs weapon deploys once more, turning and aiming at 2B, who can no longer move.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Uu‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.aaaaaaahhhhhhhhhhh!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">2B swings her sword down on her own right leg, intending to sever it.</p><p class="para"><em>(At the same time 2B cuts her leg off, Pod fires its laser)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Gaaah!!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>Firing high output laser.</code></p><p class="para"><em>(2B tosses her sword at the Pod. It hits its mark, damaging 153)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><em>(dying robot sounds)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">2B, who‚Äôd narrowly escaped the attack, tossed the sword she‚Äôd used to slice off her right leg as a counter attack on Pod 153.</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para"><code>YoRHa unit 2Bi.......tactile...un...</code></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">About 15 seconds after convulsions from the Pod, who‚Äôd taken a direct hit from the sword, it emitted a strange noise and stopped. That sound was‚Ä¶..a high-pitched laughter, like a child‚Äôs voice‚Ä¶‚Ä¶</p><p class="title" style=" font-size: 300%;">Scene 4: Message</p>
<p class="title-special title-box">2B (narration)
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">After taking down the rampaging Pod, I was stuck there, unable to move.
There seemed to be no way to easily repair the heavily damaged leg.
As I made my way over to the fallen Pod in something akin to a crawl, the Pod‚Äôs speaker activated.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Operator 6O to 2B! 2B! Can you hear me? Are you okay!?</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶This is 2B. I hear you.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Aah, 2B. Thank goodness‚Ä¶‚Ä¶
I was monitoring you from here, but Pod 153‚Äôs attack mode suddenly became impossible to control.
But the control program can only be rewritten with a code by the Pod‚Äôs original support target, 9S‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Operator 6O.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Could it be that 9S was trying to‚Ä¶..But, for 9S, of all people, to implant an attack order in the Pod and aim it at you is‚Äî</p><p class="para"><em>(2B shouts to interrupt her words)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Operator 6O!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶..Yes? What is it?</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">How long‚Ä¶..</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Come again?</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">How long have you been there?</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">Um‚Ä¶.I‚Äôm not sure what you mean‚Ä¶.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">The access point‚Äôs transmission functions have yet to be repaired.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶Huh?</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">When I went in to do a final check on the body reconstruction unit, there was a small machine fragment remaining inside.
I immediately judged the rusted piece to be part of a machine lifeform.
It seemed odd, so I left the computer terminal‚Äôs final activation untouched.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">A laser transmission would have also been impossible in the sandstorm.
In other words, you shouldn‚Äôt be capable of communicating with me from the above orbit satellite.</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">The one in Pod 153 right now‚Ä¶.who are you?</p><p class="para"><em>(8 seconds of silence)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶..Fufu‚Ä¶‚Ä¶fufufufufu.
Hey, she figured it out.
She sure did!
Ahh. And here I thought it‚Äôd be interesting to pin it all on 9S and watch them fall apart.
I thought it‚Äôd be interesting, you know?
What a bummer.
A real bummer.</p><p class="para"><em>(Operator 6O speaks as if there are two people)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">We are a unified body of thought.
We are numerous and singular.
But 2B, I wonder if it‚Äôs really our fault?</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">What are you talking about‚Ä¶‚Ä¶</p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">This incident might‚Äôve been 9S‚Äô work, you know.
Maybe he really had decided to kill you.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.</p><p class="para"><em>(2B shakes with anger, her breathing uneven)</em></p><p class="title-special title-box">6O
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">The likelihood of YorHa unit 9S accessing confidential information was high.
That‚Äôs why it was determined that an E model would deal out punishment.
He might‚Äôve realized, you know?
That the 2B who‚Äôs killed 9S time and time again‚Ä¶.is you, No. 2 Type E.</p><p class="title-special title-box">2B
  ‚Äã</p><p class="para">‚Ä¶.Ahh!!</p><p class="title-special title-box">Pod 153 (narration)
